        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 3:05PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 305 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Odessa, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Midland, Odessa, Crane, Midland International Air and Space Port,
West Odessa, Odessa Schlemeyer Field, Crane County Airport, Warfield,
Skywest Airport, and Pleasant Farms.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 106 and 136.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
